The paper deals with analyzing user profiles on different social networks, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses natural language processing techniques to measure the similarity of user profiles, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper deals with privacy and security risks, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity). The paper also uses automated classifiers, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with analyzing user behavior, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
